    <fr:title text="Disjoint coproducts are independent sums › "><fr:link href="jms-006M.xml" title="Disjoint coproducts are independent sums" addr="jms-006M" type="local">Disjoint coproducts are independent sums</fr:link> › </fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>As soon as the co-span <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{u \hookrightarrow  u+v \hookleftarrow  v\right \}\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> is independent, it evidently satisfies the universal property of <fr:link href="jms-006L.xml" title="Independent sum" addr="jms-006L" type="local">independent sums</fr:link>, which is weaker than that of coproducts. Coproduct co-spans are always independent in an extensive category.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter>
